      "s": "Trader Joe's has faced significant NLRB enforcement actions since 2022, when workers formed Trader Joe's United. An NLRB administrative law judge found the company committed 17+ labor law violations including coercive threats over union insignia, withholding retirement benefits from unionized stores, and threatening wage freezes. Trader Joe's also controversially argued the NLRB itself is unconstitutional—a tactic also used by SpaceX and Amazon—to avoid accountability for alleged unfair labor practices.",
